fields.description:
Hi,
I've downloaded a new Version of Titanium Studio (2.0.1.201204132053) on OS X Lion 10.7.3, I've installed Xcode 4.3.1 But i have problems running a simple Test Application on the iPhone Simulator, I always get this error message:

[INFO] One moment, building ...
[INFO] Titanium SDK version: 2.0.1 (04/12/12 16:33 999c68a)
[INFO] iPhone Device family: universal
[INFO] iPhone SDK version: 5.1
[INFO] iPhone simulated device: iphone
[INFO] Compiling localization files
[INFO] Launching application in Simulator
2012-05-07 00:28:50.925 osascript[20854:f07] Cannot find executable for CFBundle 0x7f9e5b432b30 </Library/ScriptingAdditions/SIMBL.osax> (not loaded)
osascript: OpenScripting.framework - scripting addition "/Library/ScriptingAdditions/SIMBL.osax" declares no loadable handlers.
[INFO] Launched application in Simulator (5.31 seconds)
[INFO] Application started
[INFO] test1/1.0 (2.0.1.GA2.999c68a)
[INFO] Application has exited from Simulator

What's goin on? I couldn't find any solutions through Google :(


Best regards,
darki777
fields.summary: iOS: Osascript - Cannot find executable for CFBundle
fields.environment:
OS X Lion 10.7.3
Titanium Studio 2.0.1.201204132053
Xcode 4.3.1
iPhone SDK 5.1

comments.body: Neeraj, I believe this is a TIMOB issue.
User has SIMBL installed and it's mess up the Applescript file that focuses the iOS Simulator. Not a Titanium problem.
Closing ticket as invalid with reference to the previous comments.
